The evidence with the title 'What happens when a country goes bust - The Economist explains ' says Nov 24, 2014  ... When a country fails to pay its creditors on time , it is said to go into “ default” , the national equivalent of going bankrupt . But sovereign defaults are quite different from business bankruptcies as it is far harder for creditors to repossess the assets of a sovereign entity than to repossess the assets of acompany  ... 
